represents a shape consisting of two or more vertices,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"specified as ","type":"text"},{"code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instances, and the line segments that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"connect them. For example, you could use an polyline to represent a road or the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"path along which something moves.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpolyline"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"role":"collection","abstract":[{"text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling.","type":"text"}],"title":"MapLibre","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/coordinate":{"title":"coordinate","type":"topic","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A coordinate representing the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"fragments":[{"text":"coordinate","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/coordinate","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/coordinate","kind":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNPointCollection":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnpointcollection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNPointCollection","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object represents a shape consisting of one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"disconnected vertices, specified as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CLLocationCoordinate2D"},{"type":"text","text":" instances. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"points in the collection may be related but are not connected spatially. For"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"example, you could use a point collection to represent all the trees in an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"orchard."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"MLNPointCollection","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","title":"MLNPointCollection"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon."}],"title":"MLNOverlay","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"title":"MLNAnnotation","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"objects to handle the display."}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNAnnotation"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","type":"topic","title":"overlayBounds","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds"}}}